      • convertDegrees

        public static java.lang.Double convertDegrees(java.lang.String s)
        Convert coordinates of the form "DD-MM-SS.XXXd" or "SS.XXX" where DD are degrees MM are minutes SS.XXX are seconds and decimal seconds d is a direction (i.e., N, S, E, or W) Conversion will FAIL if input is decimal degrees because it will be interpreted as degree seconds. The use case for this comes from parsing NFDC runway coordinates.

        Returns:
